# Vue 3 + TypeScript Standards

## Components
- Use `<script setup lang="ts">` with Composition API
- Composition over inheritance; extract reusable logic into `use*` composables
- Props via `defineProps<T>()` with explicit types — no `PropType` workarounds
- Emit via `defineEmits<{ eventName: [payload: Type] }>()`

## TypeScript
- No `any`; prefer `unknown` + type narrowing
- Validate API responses against Zod schemas (`ZodFlaw*` types in `@/types/zodFlaw`)
- Use generated OpenAPI client from `@/generated/` — never hand-roll API calls
- Run `yarn type-check` before committing

## Services & State
- API calls belong in `@/services/*Service.ts`, not in components
- Global state in Pinia stores (`@/stores/`); local state with `ref`/`computed`
- `osimRuntime` store for environment/backend config

## Security
- Sanitize HTML before rendering with `sanitize-html` (see `CommentList.vue`)
- Never use `v-html` without sanitization — add `eslint-disable` comment only with sanitized input
- Validate and encode all user-supplied URL parameters

## Scripts (run only when user asks)
- `yarn lint` — ESLint check
- `yarn type-check` — TS type validation
- `yarn test:unit` — Vitest unit tests
- `yarn vibe-check` — combined lint + type-check + tests

**Never auto-run these after implementation.** Wait for explicit user confirmation before triggering any validation pipeline.
